@langford_dev SHA-256 is a hash function known for security and speed. Keccak-256 returns a subset of 256 bits, if any bits are changed then the output is changed unpredictably.

@langford_dev A little bg info to add: hash functions map data to a bit string of fixed size and authenticate pieces of data. Regardless of input size, the output will be a fixed-length string that is unique and cannot be reverse-engineered.
